{"type":"message","id":"e084d8d2","parentId":"bcbdc9bd","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:18:02.613Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Artemis** is a figure from Greek mythology with multiple meanings:\n\n## Greek Mythology\n- **Goddess of the hunt, wilderness, wild animals, the Moon, and chastity**\n- Twin sister of Apollo (god of the sun)\n- Daughter of Zeus and Leto\n- Often depicted with a bow and arrow, accompanied by a deer or hunting dogs\n- One of the most widely venerated deities in ancient Greece\n\n## Modern Usage\n- **NASA's Artemis program** – Current mission to return humans to the Moon (named after the goddess)\n- **Artemis Fowl** – Popular fantasy book series by Eoin Colfer\n- **Various place names, ships, and organizations**\n\nThe name comes from the Greek word *artemes*, meaning \"safe\" or \"butcher.\"\n\n---\n\nAnd yes, I'll respond in English when you ask in English! No problem."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774851476535}}
