{"type":"message","id":"3e92f870","parentId":"e7f713de","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:38:50.011Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-30 14:38:49 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM | ou_ea1c6c04083c10886bdd141a0cc60ff9 [msg:om_x100b5395e946a484b31b7b7fabc5534]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5395e946a484b31b7b7fabc5534\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_ea1c6c04083c10886bdd141a0cc60ff9\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_ea1c6c04083c10886bdd141a0cc60ff9\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-30 14:38 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_ea1c6c04083c10886bdd141a0cc60ff9\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_ea1c6c04083c10886bdd141a0cc60ff9\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_ea1c6c04083c10886bdd141a0cc60ff9\"\n}\n```\n\ngive me a chart of all terminal commands with the lesser used one at the bottome, with the command, how to use and what it does"}],"timestamp":1774852730008}}
{"type":"message","id":"5bd96be7","parentId":"3e92f870","timestamp":"2026-03-30T06:40:37.136Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✗\n\nI'm working on creating a terminal commands chart for you."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.write:17","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/admin/.openclaw/workspace/terminal-commands.md","content":"# Terminal Commands Reference\n\n## Most Common Commands\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `ls` | `ls [options] [directory]` | List directory contents |\n| `cd` | `cd [directory]` | Change directory |\n| `pwd` | `pwd` | Print working directory (show current path) |\n| `cat` | `cat [file]` | Display file contents |\n| `cp` | `cp [source] [destination]` | Copy files/directories |\n| `mv` | `mv [source] [destination]` | Move/rename files |\n| `rm` | `rm [options] [file]` | Remove files/directories |\n| `mkdir` | `mkdir [directory]` | Create directory |\n| `touch` | `touch [file]` | Create empty file or update timestamp |\n| `echo` | `echo [text]` | Print text to terminal |\n\n## Frequently Used Commands\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `grep` | `grep [pattern] [file]` | Search for patterns in text |\n| `find` | `find [path] [expression]` | Search for files/directories |\n| `chmod` | `chmod [permissions] [file]` | Change file permissions |\n| `chown` | `chown [user:group] [file]` | Change file owner/group |\n| `ps` | `ps [options]` | Display running processes |\n| `kill` | `kill [PID]` | Terminate processes |\n| `top`/`htop` | `top` | Display system processes/resources |\n| `df` | `df [options]` | Show disk space usage |\n| `du` | `du [options] [path]` | Show directory/file sizes |\n| `tar` | `tar [options] [archive] [files]` | Archive/extract files |\n| `curl` | `curl [URL]` | Transfer data from/to server |\n| `wget` | `wget [URL]` | Download files from web |\n| `ssh` | `ssh [user@host]` | Secure shell remote login |\n| `scp` | `scp [source] [destination]` | Secure copy between hosts |\n| `git` | `git [command]` | Version control operations |\n\n## Moderately Used Commands\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `awk` | `awk '[pattern] {action}' [file]` | Text processing/pattern matching |\n| `sed` | `sed '[script]' [file]` | Stream editor for text manipulation |\n| `cut` | `cut [options] [file]` | Extract sections from lines |\n| `sort` | `sort [options] [file]` | Sort lines of text |\n| `uniq` | `uniq [options] [file]` | Filter duplicate lines |\n| `wc` | `wc [options] [file]` | Count words/lines/characters |\n| `head` | `head [options] [file]` | Show first lines of file |\n| `tail` | `tail [options] [file]` | Show last lines of file |\n| `less`/`more` | `less [file]` | View file contents (pager) |\n| `nano`/`vim` | `nano [file]` | Text editors |\n| `which` | `which [command]` | Locate command path |\n| `whereis` | `whereis [command]` | Locate binary/source/manual |\n| `man` | `man [command]` | Display manual pages |\n| `history` | `history` | Show command history |\n| `alias` | `alias [name]='[command]'` | Create command shortcuts |\n| `export` | `export [VAR]=[value]` | Set environment variables |\n| `env` | `env` | Show environment variables |\n| `whoami` | `whoami` | Show current username |\n| `id` | `id [user]` | Show user/group IDs |\n| `groups` | `groups [user]` | Show user's groups |\n\n## Less Common / Specialized Commands\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `tee` | `tee [options] [file]` | Redirect output to file and stdout |\n| `xargs` | `xargs [command]` | Build commands from stdin |\n| `tr` | `tr [set1] [set2]` | Translate/delete characters |\n| `diff` | `diff [file1] [file2]` | Compare files line by line |\n| `cmp` | `cmp [file1] [file2]` | Compare files byte by byte |\n| `comm` | `comm [file1] [file2]` | Compare two sorted files |\n| `join` | `join [file1] [file2]` | Join lines on common field |\n| `paste` | `paste [files]` | Merge lines of files |\n| `split` | `split [options] [file]` | Split file into pieces |\n| `csplit` | `csplit [file] [pattern]` | Split by context/patterns |\n| `nl` | `nl [file]` | Number lines of file |\n| `fold` | `fold [options] [file]` | Wrap lines to width |\n| `fmt` | `fmt [options] [file]` | Reformat paragraph text |\n| `pr` | `pr [options] [file]` | Format for printing |\n| `col` | `col [options]` | Filter reverse line feeds |\n| `column` | `column [options] [file]` | Format as columns |\n| `tac` | `tac [file]` | Concatenate reverse (cat backwards) |\n| `rev` | `rev [file]` | Reverse lines character-wise |\n| `shuf` | `shuf [file]` | Shuffle/randomize lines |\n| `stdbuf` | `stdbuf [options] [command]` | Modify stdio buffering |\n| `timeout` | `timeout [duration] [command]` | Run with time limit |\n| `nohup` | `nohup [command]` | Run immune to hangups |\n| `disown` | `disown [job]` | Remove job from shell |\n| `wait` | `wait [PID]` | Wait for process completion |\n| `jobs` | `jobs` | List active jobs |\n| `fg`/`bg` | `fg [job]` | Foreground/background jobs |\n| `trap` | `trap [action] [signals]` | Handle signals in scripts |\n| `type` | `type [command]` | Show command type |\n| `command` | `command [cmd]` | Run command bypassing aliases |\n| `builtin` | `builtin [cmd]` | Run shell builtin |\n| `enable` | `enable [builtin]` | Enable/disable shell builtins |\n| `eval` | `eval [command]` | Execute arguments as command |\n| `exec` | `exec [command]` | Replace shell with command |\n| `source`/` .` | `source [file]` | Execute commands from file |\n| `logout` | `logout` | Exit login shell |\n| `exit` | `exit [code]` | Exit with status code |\n| `set` | `set [options]` | Set shell options/variables |\n| `unset` | `unset [var]` | Remove variable/function |\n| `readonly` | `readonly [var]` | Mark variable read-only |\n| `declare`/`typeset` | `declare [options] [var]` | Declare variables with attributes |\n| `local` | `local [var]` | Create local variable in function |\n| `shift` | `shift [n]` | Shift positional parameters |\n| `getopts` | `getopts [opts] [var]` | Parse command options |\n| `umask` | `umask [mask]` | Set file creation mask |\n| `ulimit` | `ulimit [options]` | Set resource limits |\n| `times` | `times` | Show process times |\n| `caller` | `caller [frame]` | Return caller context |\n| `compgen` | `compgen [options]` | Generate completion matches |\n| `complete` | `complete [options] [cmd]` | Specify completion behavior |\n| `compopt` | `compopt [options]` | Modify completion options |\n| `bind` | `bind [options]` | Set readline key bindings |\n| `shopt` | `shopt [options] [opt]` | Toggle shell options |\n| `hash` | `hash [options]` | Remember command locations |\n| `help` | `help [command]` | Display help for builtins |\n\n## System/Network Commands (Less Common)\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `netstat` | `netstat [options]` | Network connections/statistics |\n| `ss` | `ss [options]` | Socket statistics (netstat alternative) |\n| `lsof` | `lsof [options]` | List open files |\n| `fuser` | `fuser [file]` | Show processes using file |\n| `strace` | `strace [options] [cmd]` | Trace system calls |\n| `ltrace` | `ltrace [options] [cmd]` | Trace library calls |\n| `ptrace` | `ptrace [options]` | Process trace |\n| `dmesg` | `dmesg [options]` | Print kernel messages |\n| `sysctl` | `sysctl [options]` | Configure kernel parameters |\n| `modprobe` | `modprobe [module]` | Load kernel modules |\n| `lsmod` | `lsmod` | List loaded modules |\n| `rmmod` | `rmmod [module]` | Remove kernel module |\n| `insmod` | `insmod [module]` | Insert kernel module |\n| `depmod` | `depmod` | Generate module dependencies |\n| `mknod` | `mknod [name] [type] [major] [minor]` | Create special files |\n| `losetup` | `losetup [options]` | Set up/control loop devices |\n| `mount`/`umount` | `mount [device] [dir]` | Mount/unmount filesystems |\n| `blkid` | `blkid [options]` | Locate/block device attributes |\n| `lsblk` | `lsblk [options]` | List block devices |\n| `fdisk`/`gdisk` | `fdisk [device]` | Partition table manipulators |\n| `parted` | `parted [device]` | Partition manager |\n| `mkfs` | `mkfs [options] [device]` | Create filesystem |\n| `fsck` | `fsck [options] [device]` | Check/repair filesystem |\n| `tune2fs` | `tune2fs [options] [device]` | Adjust ext filesystem params |\n|"}},{"type":"text","text":" `"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"dashscope-coding","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774852730010}}
